    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 987.2-generation Cayman S represents a pinnacle of mid-engine balance, powered by the robust 3.4L flat-six featuring Direct Fuel Injection (DFI) for optimized thermal efficiency and throttle response. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and a factory-optioned limited-slip differential, ensuring superior power delivery out of low-speed corners. The chassis utilizes MacPherson struts with reinforced subframes, providing exceptional lateral stiffness and communicative steering feedback through the hydraulic rack. Braking performance is maintained by four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers paired with internally vented and cross-drilled rotors. This example is mechanically sorted with a clean valvetrain and a dry-sump lubrication system that remains pressurized under high-G loads. While it shows honest signs of use commensurate with a well-loved driver\u2019s car, the mechanical synchronization and structural integrity are excellent.",
